01:39:37.237 --> 01:39:39.705
I'm not Eliza fucking Doolittle.
I made myself.

01:39:39.773 --> 01:39:41.764
- Those are my books.
- I'd see you all right.

01:39:41.842 --> 01:39:44.333
- I taught you.
- I taught you, too.

01:39:44.411 --> 01:39:47.141
What? How to go into a public lavatory?

01:39:48.415 --> 01:39:49.746
Anyway...

01:39:50.117 --> 01:39:53.177
if it hadn't been you,
it would have been someone else.

01:39:54.288 --> 01:39:55.983
- Sleep on it.
- How?

01:39:56.890 --> 01:39:58.858
I could give you a wank.

01:39:59.927 --> 01:40:01.827
- What do you want?
- Joe.

01:40:03.497 --> 01:40:04.555
John.

01:40:04.631 --> 01:40:05.689
I'm not John.

01:40:06.166 --> 01:40:07.565
John's dead.

01:40:10.204 --> 01:40:13.765
If you change your mind about the wank,
don't wake me up.

01:40:27.721 --> 01:40:29.848
I don't understand my life.

01:40:32.126 --> 01:40:33.923
I was an only child.

01:40:35.362 --> 01:40:37.262
I lost both my parents.

01:40:38.799 --> 01:40:41.495
By the time I was 20, I was going bald.

01:40:42.936 --> 01:40:44.597
I'm a homosexual.

01:40:47.241 --> 01:40:49.732
In the way of circumstances
and background...

01:40:49.810 --> 01:40:52.643
I had everything
an artist could possibly want.

01:40:54.481 --> 01:40:56.779
It was practically a blueprint.

01:40:58.585 --> 01:41:01.782
I was programmed to be a novelist
or a playwright.

01:41:03.724 --> 01:41:06.192
But I'm not and you are.

01:41:07.594 --> 01:41:08.686
Joe?

01:41:11.665 --> 01:41:14.099
You do everything better than me!

01:41:15.035 --> 01:41:17.299
You even sleep better than me!

01:41:46.834 --> 01:41:48.802
I should have used this.

01:41:49.770 --> 01:41:51.362
More theatrical.

01:41:52.739 --> 01:41:55.401
But you'd have spotted that straight away.

01:42:27.808 --> 01:42:29.207
I loved him.

01:42:30.677 --> 01:42:32.577
I must have loved him.

01:42:34.047 --> 01:42:36.015
I chose him to kill me.

01:43:33.473 --> 01:43:36.033
I was scheduled to pick him up at 12:00.

01:43:36.109 --> 01:43:37.633
A private lunch.

01:43:38.812 --> 01:43:41.542
He leads an increasingly glamorous life.

01:43:47.454 --> 01:43:49.251
Is he a heavy sleeper?

01:43:49.323 --> 01:43:52.019
I know nothing about his personal life.

01:43:52.626 --> 01:43:55.686
Idle curiosity has never been
my strong point.

01:43:56.997 --> 01:43:59.363
Try looking through the letterbox.

01:44:03.503 --> 01:44:04.902
Hello, Mr. Orton.

01:44:05.572 --> 01:44:10.009
Personally, I've driven in the firm's car,
but different destinations.

01:44:12.012 --> 01:44:14.173
Has the other got a bald head?

01:44:14.815 --> 01:44:17.249
No, he wears a wig.

01:44:21.588 --> 01:44:23.681
Can you break down this door?

01:44:24.024 --> 01:44:25.321
Clifford!

01:44:25.659 --> 01:44:27.752
Can we break down the door?

01:44:27.828 --> 01:44:29.318
Certainly not.

01:44:29.429 --> 01:44:32.489
If there's damage to be done, call the police.

01:44:32.933 --> 01:44:34.298
That's their job.

01:44:44.378 --> 01:44:48.144
If he hadn't murdered Joe,
nobody would ever have known his name.

01:44:48.215 --> 01:44:50.046
Ken was the first wife.

01:44:50.717 --> 01:44:52.878
Did all the work and the waiting, and then...

01:44:56.823 --> 01:44:59.883
First wives don't usually
beat their husbands' heads in.

01:44:59.960 --> 01:45:02.121
No, though why, I can't think.

01:45:02.696 --> 01:45:05.597
So what does that make you?
The second wife?

01:45:06.099 --> 01:45:07.999
Better than that, dear.

01:45:08.969 --> 01:45:10.095
The widow.

01:45:21.381 --> 01:45:23.178
<i>There were two ceremonies.</i>

01:45:23.250 --> 01:45:26.686
<i>Joe's at Golders Green.</i>
<i>Everybody there. House full.</i>

01:45:27.421 --> 01:45:30.413
<i>Ken's at Enfield.</i>
<i>You couldn't give tickets away.</i>

01:45:30.490 --> 01:45:31.582
<i>Three people.</i>

01:45:31.658 --> 01:45:32.989
<i>That's sad.</i>

01:45:34.361 --> 01:45:35.453
<i>Well...</i>

01:45:36.863 --> 01:45:39.388
<i>they fetched up together at the end.</i>

01:45:41.401 --> 01:45:43.835
Strictly speaking,
we would have preferred it...

01:45:43.904 --> 01:45:47.169
if both the deceased
had been cremated on the premises.

01:45:47.240 --> 01:45:51.108
Intermingling would then have been
carried out by experienced personnel...

01:45:51.178 --> 01:45:53.339
under controlled conditions.

01:46:05.826 --> 01:46:09.387
I think I'm putting in more of Joe
than I am of Kenneth.

01:46:11.865 --> 01:46:14.390
It's a gesture, dear, not a recipe.

01:46:22.275 --> 01:46:25.472
I hope nobody gets to hear about this
in Leicester.

